messages.message:
@Bastiane did you already follow-up with Mitch on these questions?

I imagine that the behavior will be similar to our current split-classification Flow step in the enterprise platform. An input file will be split into records and each record will have a class label. It will then run extraction using that class's fields. For example, if an input file has a W2 followed by 2 paystubs, the W2 doc will be processed with the W2 fields, and paystubs will be processed by paystub fields. In the App results page, you'll see 3 sets of fields (1 W2, and 2 paystub), similar to if you had 3 files (1 W2, 2 paystubs)
@Mitch Welzen would love any feedback from the field on if this makes sense, and if there are other requirements we should consider
Yes, we discussed this in one of the meetings with field team. But let us know if there's any additional feedback
